                            <comment id="13548931" author="yukim" created="Wed, 9 Jan 2013 20:03:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like user defined compaction has not been working since data directory structure change in 1.1.&lt;br/&gt;
Patch fixes this by pointing proper directory based on given file names.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13549055" author="mkjellman" created="Wed, 9 Jan 2013 21:49:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 verified this patch works against 1.2.0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13549061" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 9 Jan 2013 21:52:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LGTM.  Can you also add a quick test for forceUserDefinedCompaction to catch this regression?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also created &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-5139&quot; title=&quot;Drop keyspace argument from forceUserDefinedCompactions&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-5139&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-5139&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for followup.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13549841" author="yukim" created="Thu, 10 Jan 2013 17:58:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed with the test added to CompactionsTest.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13563458" author="JIRAUSER308715" created="Sat, 26 Jan 2013 11:57:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;FYI it worked, you just had to put the dir name in the string: so forceUserDefinedCompaction ks cf/ks-cf-hf-80-Data.db&lt;br/&gt;
Should put something in NEWS.txt for anyone who figured that out and was using forceUserDefinedCompaction.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
